{"id":840,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":840,"title":"Melchizedek","subtitle":"","short_title":"Melchizedek","uri":"/scriptures/bd/melchizedek","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/melchizedek.t1","order":".000.2198"},[".title","Melchizedek"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/melchizedek.p1","order":".000.2199"},["i","King of Righteousness."],"A notable prophet and leader who lived about 2000",["span.small","B.C."],"He is called the king of Salem (Jerusalem), king of peace, and “priest of the most High God.” Unfortunately, information concerning him in the Bible is relatively scarce, being limited to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/14.18-20"},"Gen. 14:18–20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/5.6"},"Heb. 5:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/7.1-3"},"7:1–3"],". Mention of the priesthood of Melchizedek is given in several other instances, primarily in Psalms and in Hebrews. However, latter-day revelation gives us much more about him and his priesthood (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/14.18d"},["span.small","JST"],"Gen. 14:17 [Gen. 14:18 note",["i","d"],"]"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst-gen/14.25-40"},["span.small","JST"],"Gen. 14:25–40"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst-heb/7.3"},["span.small","JST"],"Heb. 7:3 [Appendix]"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/13.14-19"},"Alma 13:14–19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.14"},"D&C 84:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/107.1-4"},"107:1–4"],"). From these sources we realize something of the greatness of this prophet and the grandeur of his ministry. See also",["i",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/jebus"},"Jebus"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/jerusalem"},"Jerusalem"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/melchizedek-priesthood"},"Melchizedek Priesthood"],"."]]]],"refs":null}
